                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.79620 Boeing Airplane Co./26: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gade</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-11T21:00:00-03:30">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 11, 1928—9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 12—3:52 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>16. My telegram No. 15, May 11, 10 a.m. O’Neill was unaccompanied on flight, is
                    expected to leave hospital tomorrow.<note n="11" xml:id="d672fn11">For further
                        activities of Captain O’Neill, see <ref target="#pg_825">pp. 825</ref>
                        ff.</note> Aeroplane badly damaged.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gade</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
